\f0\b 3. Which real-data periods must be hard economic gates?
\f1\b0 \

\f0\b Context.
\f1\b0 \'a0The current intent requires complete real TECL history, recent performance, and predeclared rolling views. Requiring every possible slice to win is different from requiring a small fixed contract and may contradict the decision that a Gold strategy can have known regime weaknesses.\

\f0\b Suggested answer.
\f1\b0 \'a0Make complete observed TECL history and a fixed trailing-five-year horizon hard gates. Use a small predeclared rolling-window contract for generalization, but do not require every individual rolling window to exceed the full Gold margin. Instead calibrate an aggregate passage rule plus a catastrophic-window veto on controls.\

