\f0\b 6. Should Phase 1 choose expanding or rolling training windows now?
\f1\b0 \

\f0\b Context.
\f1\b0 \'a0Expanding windows use all earlier history and are more data-efficient. Fixed rolling windows emphasize current regimes but discard older evidence. TECL has too little independent history to select one by intuition.\

\f0\b Suggested answer.
\f1\b0 \'a0Do not lock the window lengths now. Compare an expanding rolling-origin spine and a recent fixed-window variant on the same null, planted-signal, regime-change, and low-trade controls. Pick the smallest design with the best future-error calibration and acceptable false-Gold/false-reject behavior.\

\f0\b Reasoning.
\f1\b0 \'a0The right answer depends on how quickly the simulated process changes and how much power is lost by shortening the training sample.\

