\f0\b 7. What role should CPCV have?
\f1\b0 \

\f0\b Context.
\f1\b0 \'a0A 2024 paper found CPCV better than walk-forward in its synthetic/ML experiment. Another study found chronology-preserving forward validation better under several non-stationary processes. CPCV can use observations later than an earlier test block for training, so it is not a historical deployment replay.\

\f0\b Suggested answer.
\f1\b0 \'a0Treat CPCV as a complementary candidate for selection stability, not an automatic Gold gate or replacement for rolling-origin. Admit it only when Montauk has a real overlapping-label problem and the Phase 1 ablation shows incremental defect detection.\

\f0\b Reasoning.
\f1\b0 \'a0This captures CPCV's benefit without mistaking more combinations for more independent regimes or future evidence.\

\f0\b Max's answer.\

\f1\b0 Use both? Ideally a gold worthy strategy should be able to pass CPCV and walk forward \
