\f0\b 8. How should purge and embargo lengths be chosen?
\f1\b0 \

\f0\b Context.
\f1\b0 \'a0Purging removes training labels/outcomes that overlap a test interval. Embargo addresses a specified residual leakage/dependence path. A copied percentage is not automatically correct, and an ordinary past-looking indicator window is not itself future leakage.\

\f0\b Suggested answer.
\f1\b0 \'a0Derive purge and embargo from the declared information interval of each label, feature, and holding outcome. Use zero when no overlap path exists. Reject any family whose required interval cannot be computed exactly.\

\f0\b Reasoning.
\f1\b0 \'a0This makes leakage control causal and testable instead of ceremonial.\

\f0\b Max's answer.
